  "name": "RPlog_Interrogation_of_Korynn_Part_2",
  "title": "The Interrogation of Director Fleming, Continued",
  "summary": "In the interrogation chamber of the I2SD Inquisitor, ISB Agent Dreven Mercurio resumes the questioning of his captured superior, Director Korynn Fleming, now Prisoner 198A and suspended in a bacta tank. Mercurio jolts him awake with electrical torture and presses to learn who placed Fleming in carbonite, why, and the meaning of the CSA-marked grav-lifts found holding him aloft. Fleming, defiant and proud, maintains that COMPNOR has already made men like them unbreakable, endures a near-fatal shock that briefly stops his heart, and then a device that explosively tears the embedded probes from his flesh. He explains his abduction occurred at a spaceborne Hutt facility during a surveillance operation on Theseus Station, naming the Corporate Sector Authority as his prime suspect. After enduring further torment without yielding any compromise, Fleming demands to be released to the Select Committee, and Mercurio finally walks away. An aftermath note records that Fleming was later cleared for duty by the Committee, the involvement of Malign or Vadim unknown.",
